cover numerous subjects.

00:31:36.100 --> 00:31:37.890
But most of these
subjects are pertaining

00:31:37.890 --> 00:31:42.990
to the Soviet Union
and North Korea.

00:31:42.990 --> 00:31:47.010
In a-- these records consists
of a variety of types of things.

00:31:47.010 --> 00:31:50.690
Everything from official
correspondence to office files,

00:31:50.690 --> 00:31:55.620
personnel files, printed
materials, things like books,

00:31:55.620 --> 00:31:59.030
periodicals, magazines,
newspapers,

00:31:59.030 --> 00:32:01.620
both in various types,
photographs,

00:32:01.620 --> 00:32:05.380
propaganda leaflets,
things like that.

00:32:08.860 --> 00:32:12.750
OK. The great majority of the
records that were captured are

00:32:12.750 --> 00:32:16.080
in either Russian, or in Korea.

00:32:16.080 --> 00:32:18.510
But there are also some
materials in other languages

00:32:18.510 --> 00:32:23.920
such as Bulgarian, Chinese,
Japanese, Polish, Hungarian.

00:32:23.920 --> 00:32:26.240
Pretty much any type of printed
materials that would have been

00:32:26.240 --> 00:32:29.500
on the Korean Peninsula at that
time could have gotten scooped

00:32:29.500 --> 00:32:33.250
up by UN forces as they
had in North basically.

